Feature: the centralized scheduled poll tracks fabro as a baked dependency so a newer fabro release bumps the bc-base pin and rebuilds :latest

  SLICE 1 of the fabro launch path (epic lead-6k1r, S1), poll-tracking leg. Once
  fabro is baked into bc-base (scenario 73 @scenario_hash:a3512aedb8763150), it
  must be maintained the SAME way the other baked dependencies are: enrolled in
  the single centralized scheduled bc-launcher poll (ADR-022 D2; scenarios 57
  @scenario_hash:930a6a6579e2a859, 58 @scenario_hash:0f386f31857fbeb1, 59
  @scenario_hash:5b6a931a493971a6) that resolves each dep's latest release and
  bump-then-rebuild-republishes :latest when a pin has advanced. This scenario
  pins the DISTINCT behavior that fabro is IN that watched-dependency set, mapped
  to its canonical PUBLIC release source fabro-sh/fabro (a GitHub-Releases Rust
  binary, downloaded like beads/steveyegge/beads rather than a pip VCS pin —
  see findings/fabro-spike/00a-fabro-tool.md).

  COMPOSITION, not retirement: this scenario COMPOSES with 57/58/59 and does NOT
  modify or retire them. It is NET-NEW and pins fabro specifically; the retirement
  set for S1 is EMPTY. (Scenario 58's Examples table could ALTERNATIVELY be
  extended BC-side to add the fabro row — see the possible-import flag in the
  dispatch note — but that would re-author 58's block; this fabro-specific pin
  keeps 58 untouched.)

  VERSION-COUPLING GUARD (ADR-051 D3): the fail-closed loop guarantee (S5/S6)
  rests on three fabro v0.254.0 mechanism facts. A poll-driven fabro bump that
  advances past v0.254.0 and touches any of those three facts REOPENS that
  guarantee and must re-verify S5/S6 before the new :latest is trusted. This
  scenario pins the ENROLLMENT + bump-rebuild mechanics only; the re-verify gate
  is a named ADR-051 D3 follow-up (S1 risk note), not asserted in this block.
  (Targets shopsystem-bc-launcher.)

  @scenario_hash:4fc67c610cba6227
  Scenario: the centralized poll enrolls fabro as a baked dependency against fabro-sh/fabro and bump-rebuilds :latest on a newer release
    Given the bc-base Dockerfile in shopsystem-bc-launcher bakes fabro at pin "v0.254.0" as a baked dependency alongside shop-templates, shop-msg, scenarios, and beads
    And the single centralized scheduled bc-launcher workflow is the one poll that check-bump-rebuilds bc-base for its baked dependencies
    When the workflow's dependency check runs and its executable body, with YAML comment lines excluded, is inspected
    Then the executable body enumerates "fabro" mapped to its canonical public release source "fabro-sh/fabro"
    And a "fabro" to "fabro-sh/fabro" mapping present only in a descriptive YAML comment, absent from the executable body, does not satisfy this enrollment
    And the fabro latest-release lookup reads the public "fabro-sh/fabro" releases using the workflow's own "GITHUB_TOKEN" and references no "BC_LAUNCHER_DISPATCH_TOKEN" or any other cross-repo dispatch credential
    And when the resolved latest fabro release tag differs from the baked "v0.254.0" pin, the workflow first mutates the Dockerfile fabro pin to the resolved tag, then rebuilds bc-base and republishes "ghcr.io/dstengle/shopsystem-bc-base:latest" at the new digest
    And a bare rebuild that left the Dockerfile fabro pin at "v0.254.0" would not satisfy this behavior
